{"TopicId":219754,"ForumId":200,"TopicTitle":"Control surfaces deploy in opposite directions","CreatedByName":"kicka55","CreatedById":227402,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-02T21:02:17Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"kicka55","CreatedById":227402,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-02T21:02:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.4.1 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 11 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0i7 6700K | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A01080 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E16 GB DDR3\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen you build a plane and try to use control surfaces as flaps by just deploying them, they deploy in opposite directions and you can\u0027t make them deploy otherwise because if you invert one, both invert. So the workaround is to break the symmetry. Can be considered a bug I think.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022fI9INM0.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002283.35\u0022 height=\u0022846\u0022 width=\u00221015\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/fI9INM0.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-10-03T00:18:01Z\u0022 title=\u002210/03/2023 12:18  AM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Oct 3\u0022\u003EOctober 3, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Anth12\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}